# C++ Naming

For new or edited C++ identifiers, prefer camel-style names such as `taskId`,
`socketManager`, and `registrationHashes`.

Avoid introducing snake_case or trailing-underscore names for implementation
variables, members, methods, and local structs unless matching an existing
external API or third-party type.

Do not rename externally visible strings or schema keys just for style. Keep
JSON fields, metric labels, protocol tag strings, environment variable names,
and persisted/wire string values unchanged unless the user explicitly asks for a
contract change.
